subSubSection.paragraph:
This species can be readily distinguished from other members of the 

Volucella pellucens

group by its longer abdominal tergite 2 (longer than tergite 3, or at most 2.4x wider than long; 
Figs. 5A, C
). Males can be further differentiated by their basoflagellomeres in lateral view slightly constricted in middle (
Fig. 1C
) and the surstyli greatly shortened in lateral view (
Figs. 1G, H
).
